37// static
38int LiftoffAssembler::NextSpillOffset(ValueKind kind, int top_spill_offset) {
39 int offset = top_spill_offset + SlotSizeForType(kind);
40 if (NeedsAlignment(kind)) {
41 offset = RoundUp(offset, SlotSizeForType(kind));
42 }
43 return offset;
44}
45
46int LiftoffAssembler::NextSpillOffset(ValueKind kind) {
47 return NextSpillOffset(kind, TopSpillOffset());
48}
49
50int LiftoffAssembler::TopSpillOffset() const {
51 return cache_state_.stack_state.empty()
52 ? StaticStackFrameSize()
53 : cache_state_.stack_state.back().offset();
54}
55
56void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegister(ValueKind kind, LiftoffRegister reg) {
57 DCHECK_EQ(reg_class_for(kind), reg.reg_class());
58 cache_state_.inc_used(reg);
59 cache_state_.stack_state.emplace_back(kind, reg, NextSpillOffset(kind));
60}
61
62// Assumes that the exception is in {kReturnRegister0}. This is where the
63// exception is stored by the unwinder after a throwing call.
64void LiftoffAssembler::PushException() {
65 LiftoffRegister reg{kReturnRegister0};
66 // This is used after a call, so {kReturnRegister0} is not used yet.
67 DCHECK(cache_state_.is_free(reg));
68 cache_state_.inc_used(reg);
69 cache_state_.stack_state.emplace_back(kRef, reg, NextSpillOffset(kRef));
70}
71
72void LiftoffAssembler::PushConstant(ValueKind kind, int32_t i32_const) {
73 V8_ASSUME(kind == kI32 || kind == kI64);
74 cache_state_.stack_state.emplace_back(kind, i32_const, NextSpillOffset(kind));
75}
76
77void LiftoffAssembler::PushStack(ValueKind kind) {
78 cache_state_.stack_state.emplace_back(kind, NextSpillOffset(kind));
79}
80
81void LiftoffAssembler::LoadToFixedRegister(VarState slot, LiftoffRegister reg) {
82 DCHECK(slot.is_const() || slot.is_stack());
83 if (slot.is_const()) {
84 LoadConstant(reg, slot.constant());
85 } else {
86 Fill(reg, slot.offset(), slot.kind());
87 }
88}
89
90void LiftoffAssembler::PopToFixedRegister(LiftoffRegister reg) {
91 DCHECK(!cache_state_.stack_state.empty());
92 VarState slot = cache_state_.stack_state.back();
93 cache_state_.stack_state.pop_back();
94 if (V8_LIKELY(slot.is_reg())) {
95 cache_state_.dec_used(slot.reg());
96 if (slot.reg() == reg) return;
97 if (cache_state_.is_used(reg)) SpillRegister(reg);
98 Move(reg, slot.reg(), slot.kind());
99 return;
100 }
101 if (cache_state_.is_used(reg)) SpillRegister(reg);
102 LoadToFixedRegister(slot, reg);
103}

105void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFixedArrayLengthAsInt32(LiftoffRegister dst,
106 Register array,
107 LiftoffRegList pinned) {
108 int offset = FixedArray::kLengthOffset - kHeapObjectTag;
109 LoadSmiAsInt32(dst, array, offset);
110}
111
112void LiftoffAssembler::LoadSmiAsInt32(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
113 int32_t offset) {
114 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
115#if V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN
116 DCHECK_EQ(kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize, 4 * kBitsPerByte);
117 offset += 4;
118#endif
119 Load(dst, src_addr, no_reg, offset, LoadType::kI32Load);
120 } else {
121 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
122 Load(dst, src_addr, no_reg, offset, LoadType::kI32Load);
123 emit_i32_sari(dst.gp(), dst.gp(), kSmiTagSize);
124 }
125}

127void LiftoffAssembler::emit_ptrsize_add(Register dst, Register lhs,
128 Register rhs) {
129 if constexpr (kSystemPointerSize == 8) {
130 emit_i64_add(LiftoffRegister(dst), LiftoffRegister(lhs),
131 LiftoffRegister(rhs));
132 } else {
133 emit_i32_add(dst, lhs, rhs);
134 }
135}

194void LiftoffAssembler::bailout(LiftoffBailoutReason reason,
195 const char* detail) {
196 DCHECK_NE(kSuccess, reason);
197 if (bailout_reason_ != kSuccess) return;
198 AbortCompilation();
199 bailout_reason_ = reason;
200 bailout_detail_ = detail;
201}

207#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_32_BIT

209namespace liftoff {
210template <void (LiftoffAssembler::*op)(Register, Register, Register)>
211void EmitI64IndependentHalfOperation(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
212 LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
213 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
214 // If {dst.low_gp()} does not overlap with {lhs.high_gp()} or {rhs.high_gp()},
215 // just first compute the lower half, then the upper half.
216 if (dst.low() != lhs.high() && dst.low() != rhs.high()) {
217 (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
218 (assm->*op)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
219 return;
220 }
221 // If {dst.high_gp()} does not overlap with {lhs.low_gp()} or {rhs.low_gp()},
222 // we can compute this the other way around.
223 if (dst.high() != lhs.low() && dst.high() != rhs.low()) {
224 (assm->*op)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
225 (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
226 return;
227 }
228 // Otherwise, we need a temporary register.
229 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs}).gp();
230 (assm->*op)(tmp, lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
231 (assm->*op)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
232 assm->Move(dst.low_gp(), tmp, kI32);
233}
234
235template <void (LiftoffAssembler::*op)(Register, Register, int32_t)>
236void EmitI64IndependentHalfOperationImm(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
237 LiftoffRegister dst,
238 LiftoffRegister lhs, int64_t imm) {
239 int32_t low_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm);
240 int32_t high_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm >> 32);
241 // If {dst.low_gp()} does not overlap with {lhs.high_gp()},
242 // just first compute the lower half, then the upper half.
243 if (dst.low() != lhs.high()) {
244 (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), low_word);
245 (assm->*op)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), high_word);
246 return;
247 }
248 // If {dst.high_gp()} does not overlap with {lhs.low_gp()},
249 // we can compute this the other way around.
250 if (dst.high() != lhs.low()) {
251 (assm->*op)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), high_word);
252 (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), low_word);
253 return;
254 }
255 // Otherwise, we need a temporary register.
256 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs}).gp();
257 (assm->*op)(tmp, lhs.low_gp(), low_word);
258 (assm->*op)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), high_word);
259 assm->Move(dst.low_gp(), tmp, kI32);
260}
261} // namespace liftoff

263void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_and(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
264 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
265 liftoff::EmitI64IndependentHalfOperation<&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_and>(
266 this, dst, lhs, rhs);
267}

299void LiftoffAssembler::emit_u32_to_uintptr(Register dst, Register src) {
300 if (dst != src) Move(dst, src, kI32);
301}

303void LiftoffAssembler::emit_u32_to_uintptr_unconditional(Register dst) {
